<TITLE> Tension runs high at DMC over Rajib killing </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 14 (bdnews24.com)Hostility and tension are running high at Dhaka Medical College over the death of Abul Asad Rajib, a leader of Bangladesh Chhatra League, the student wing of ruling Awami League. Adherents of the BCL group on Rajib's side took out a procession on the campus on Thursday morning demanding trial of the killers. Students from the rival 'Ronnie-Bidyut Barua Group' brought out another procession afterwards. They burned up a banner demanding trial of the killers of Rajib, tore down posters and beat up one from the rival group. Police have been posted on the campus and in the dormitories after the processions, officer-in-charge of Shahbagh Police Station Rezaul Karim told bdnews24.com. Rajib was fatally injured during a clash at Fazle Rabbi Hostel of the country's premier medical college on Mar 30. He died at the combined military hospital the next day. Around 30 others were injured in the clash. The college remained closed until Apr 8 after the clashes and students were asked to leave hostels. DMC chief assistant Mahbubul Haque filed a case mentioning the first clash without accusing anyone. After Rajib's death, his father Reaz Uddin Sardar lodged a complaint at the Lalbagh Police Station accusing 11. The complaint was appended to the original case. Police arrested Kamrul Islam and Muradul Islam following the complaint. The court approved a petition for murder case following the complaint, said officer-in-charge of Lalbagh Police Station Golam Rahman. The Detective Branch of police are investigating the case, he said. b
